         </origination>
         <physdesc encodinganalog="MARC 300" label="Quantity:"><extent>2 cubic feet</extent></physdesc>
         <physdesc label="Forms of Material:">Correspondence, photographs, reports, papers,
            blueprints.</physdesc>
         <repository label="Repository:">Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell
            University Library</repository>
         <abstract label="Abstract:">Correspondence, minutes, reports, photographs, blueprints, and
            other material pertaining to the Cafeteria Management (later Institution Management)
            departments, and other matters pertaining to industrial nutrition and education.
            Includes papers of Kathleen Cutlar, Alice Burgoin and Katherine W. Harris.</abstract>
         <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language>
         </langmaterial>
      </did>
      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="organization" id="a2">ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY </head>
         <p>In 1969 the Department of Institution Management and the Department of Food and
            Nutrition merged to become the Department of Human Nutrition and Food.</p>
         <p>In 1974 the Board of Trustees voted to abolish the Department of Human Nutrition and
            Food in the College of Human Ecology and the Graduate School of Nutrition to establish
            the Division of Nutritional Sciences, an intercollege unit within the Colleges of
            Agriculture and Life Sciences and Human Ecology.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Correspondence, minutes, reports, photographs, blueprints, and other material pertaining
            to the Cafeteria Management (later Institution Management) departments, including the
            papers of a professor of Institutional Management, Kathleen Cutlar. Subjects include the
            Purnell Project, "Training Schools," classroom activities, planning of Martha Van
            Rensselaer Hall, and other matters pertaining to industrial nutrition and education.
            Includes papers of Alice Burgoin and Katherine W. Harris.</p>
      </scopecontent>
